==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redemptorist
<hw>Re*demp"tor*ist</hw> <pr>(-t?r*?st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧demptoriste</ets>, fr. L. <ets>redemptor</ets> redeemer,
from <ets>redinere</ets>. See <er>Redeem</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(R.C.Ch.)</fld> <def>One of the Congregation of the Most Holy
Redeemer, founded in Naples in 1732 by St. Alphonsus Maria de Liquori.
It was introduced onto the United States in 1832 at Detroit. The Fathers
of the Congregation devote themselves to preaching to the neglected,
esp. in missions and retreats, and are forbidden by their rule to engage
in the instruction of youth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redemptory</ent>⟦br⟧
